    "In the case of the former, sentience (and therefore trust in AI) becomes a potential issue.",
    "Richman et al. (2019) provide a detailed account of model risk and note that the majority of risk controls related to models require the actuary to \"step through the calculations required by a model to produce its predictions (simulatability) or to investigate particular aspects of one part of the model in isolation, say a particular model coefficient (decomposability)\".",
